        where books are banned, and firemen burn them. The story follows Guy
        Montag, a fireman who becomes disillusioned with his role in suppressing
        knowledge. Influenced by his free-spirited neighbor Clarisse and a
        series of unsettling events, Montag begins to question his society’s
        values and seeks enlightenment through literature. Along the way, he
        encounters characters like his wife Mildred, who is numbed by mindless
        entertainment, and Faber, a former professor who helps him in his quest.
        The novel explores themes of censorship, conformity, and the power of
        books.
