        condition. After a severe seizure, Caine participates in a drug trial
        that enhances his cognitive abilities, allowing him to predict future
        events with remarkable accuracy. As he navigates this newfound power, he
        becomes entangled in a deadly game involving the mafia, the CIA, and a
        mysterious organization. Caine's journey is marked by intense action,
        complex characters, and thought-provoking questions about free will and
        determinism. The novel masterfully blends scientific concepts with a
        gripping narrative, keeping readers on the edge of their seats. Fawer’s
        ability to explain intricate mathematical theories in an accessible way
        adds depth to the story without detracting from its pace.
